               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 1ra-105vb)
 -
                     Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols. 1ra-12ra)
 - Maṣḥaf za-wäḍʾat
                     ʾǝm-ʾIyarusalem “Book that Came from Jerusalem” (fols. 12ra-18va)
 - Homily
                     by St Jacob of Serug for the funeral of priests and deacons (fols.
                     52rb-56ra)
 - Homily by archbishop ʾabbā Sawiros (fols. 65va-67vb)
 -
                     Homily by ʾabbā Salāmā, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols.75va-80ra)
 II)
                     Ṣalota śǝryätä ḫaṭiʾat “Prayer of Absolution of Sins” (fols. 106ra-111rb), (cp.
                     EMML no. 427(9)).
 
 Colophon</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#105vb">105vb</locus>: ተፈጸመ፡ ጽሒፈ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ፍትሐት፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡
                        አሜን።<locus target="#105vb">105vb</locus>: The writing of the Book of
                        Absolution has been completed in the peace of God, Amen. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
