                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor; a few lines on the
                           incipit page of Text I, alternating with black lines; two initial lines
                           of Text II; two initial lines of each section of the text; names of
                           Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (fol. 39va); parts of abbreviations; elements
                           of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements; some other
                           words, e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 2vb, 3ra, 4rb), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g.,
                           fols. 7rb, 8vb, 9ra), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 7rb, 8ra, 13va), nǝbäl (fols.
                           7va, 8rb), wa-yǝbälu (fols. 12va, 16va), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 21ra, 38ra,
                           46rb), qǝdmä (e.g., fols. 31rb, 32va, 36vb), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g, fols. 33va,
                           35va, 36vb).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
